# Routing System

Titan uses a centralized routing system that supports dynamic parameters and middleware injection.

### Basic Routes

Define routes in your controller files using decorators or the fluent API.

```typescript
import { Controller, Get } from '@titan/core';

@Controller('/users')
export class UserController {

  @Get('/')
  index() {
    return { message: 'List of users' };
  }

  @Get('/:id')
  show(req: Request) {
    const { id } = req.params;
    return { userId: id };
  }
}
```

### Route Groups

You can group routes to apply middleware or prefixes collectively.

```typescript
Router.group('/api', () => {
  // Routes defined here will have /api prefix
}).middleware([AuthMiddleware]);
```

