# Active Record ORM

Titan includes a powerful ORM inspired by Laravel Eloquent and Active Record patterns. It supports PostgreSQL, MySQL, and SQLite.

### Defining Models

Models represent tables in your database.

```typescript
import { Model, Column, PrimaryKey } from '@titan/orm';

export class User extends Model {
  @PrimaryKey()
  id: number;

  @Column()
  email: string;

  @Column({ name: 'created_at' })
  createdAt: Date;
}
```

### Querying Data

Fetching data is intuitive and chainable.

```typescript
// Find all active users
const users = await User.where('active', true).get();

// Find by ID
const user = await User.find(1);
```

# Database Migrations

Version control your database schema. Migrations allow you to modify your database structure safely.

### Creating a Migration

Use the CLI to generate a new migration file.

```bash
titan make:migration create_posts_table
```

### Migration Structure

The file contains an `up` method to apply changes and a `down` method to revert them.

```typescript
export class CreatePostsTable {
  async up(schema: Schema) {
    await schema.createTable('posts', (table) => {
      table.increments('id');
      table.string('title');
      table.text('content');
      table.timestamps();
    });
  }

  async down(schema: Schema) {
    await schema.dropTable('posts');
  }
}
```

# Caching Strategies

Improve response times by caching frequently accessed data. Titan supports Redis and in-memory caching.

### Basic Usage

```typescript
import { Cache } from '@titan/cache';

// Store data for 60 minutes
await Cache.put('user:1', userData, 60);

// Retrieve data
const user = await Cache.get('user:1');

// Remove data
await Cache.forget('user:1');
```

### Cache Aside Pattern

This pattern involves checking the cache first; if data is missing, fetch from DB and populate the cache.

```typescript
let user = await Cache.get('user:1');
if (!user) {
  user = await User.find(1);
  await Cache.put('user:1', user);
}
return user;
```

# Job Queues

Offload heavy processing tasks to a background queue to keep your API snappy. Perfect for sending emails or processing images.

### Defining Jobs

```typescript
import { Job, Dispatch } from '@titan/queue';

@Job('SendEmail')
export class SendEmailJob {
  async handle(data: any) {
    // Logic to send email
    console.log(`Sending email to ${data.to}`);
  }
}
```

### Dispatching Jobs

```typescript
import { Dispatch } from '@titan/queue';

await Dispatch(new SendEmailJob({ to: 'user@example.com' }));
```
